'''Operation Blue Plug''' was an operation planned by [[General/Legends|General]] [[Garm Bel Iblis/Legends|Garm Bel Iblis]] to retake the key system of [[Commenor/Legends|Commenor]], following the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic's]] recapture of [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]]. The plan was never put into motion because the people of Commenor ousted the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Governor/Legends|governor]] on their own a short time later.

The entire plan was quietly classified and forgotten until about [[40 ABY/Legends|40 ABY]], during the [[Second Galactic Civil War]], when it was claimed in the [[Chasin Document]] that the [[Galactic Federation of Free Alliances|Galactic Alliance]] was planning to invade Commenor. [[Tycho Celchu/Legends|Tycho Celchu]], being familiar with some of the tactics used by Bel Iblis, became suspicious that the Chasin Document was actually a revision of Blue Plug. He asked his wife, [[Winter Celchu]], to conduct an investigation to determine if the still-classified Blue Plug documents had been sliced into. Winter discovered that the Alliance's backup code had indeed been sliced using a [[Galactic Alliance Guard]] [[Three seven nine aitch oh ell forty-four underscore bee nine two one|passcode]] and had been altered to send files to a [[Lumiya|spy]]. The military networks were scrubbed of the [[Spy/Legends|spy's]] code, and Winter's findings were turned over to [[Galactic Alliance Intelligence Service]]. Tycho and Winter presented their findings to a group of Galactic Alliance military personnel, including [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Cha Niathal|Niathal]] and [[Colonel/Legends|Colonel]] [[Darth Caedus|Jacen Solo]], who was infuriated about the implication of GAG in the security breach. Upon checking the code in his [[Datapad/Legends|datapad]], however, he determined that the passcode was on a list of unassigned passcodes.

